        "right_heading": "You Activate the Zinc Ions",
        "right_text": "<p>When the two solutions come together, a chemical reaction occurs that instantly releases billions of zinc ions.</p><p>When you first pour the rinse, you’ll notice it’s green. That means the solution is freshly activated and the zinc ions are ready to bind to germs.</p><p>But, if you wait 5 minutes after pouring, you’ll notice the poured mouthwash turns blue. That means the zinc ions are no longer as effective at preventing bad breath.</p><p>So remember, always use SmartMouth™ immediately after pouring!</p>",
